were just bashing the junk out of the necro pet.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As Sydia pointed out, that's solely due to the smaller attack range of the skeletons.  When a mob is rooted(i.e. you're using an earth pet), it will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> always</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> attack whatever target is closest to them.  You could have an earth pet do 98% of the damage to a mob, with /pet taunt on, and anyone who runs by and gets closer than the pet will get hit.  Aggro accumulated, taunting, and damage dealt mean <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> nothing</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when dealing with rooted mobs.<br>
<br>
Even when not rooted, necro pets still tend to get hit more often because they're closer. <p><hr width=335 align=LEFT><font color=007100><b>Mathas Oakheart</b></font> - 60th Hierophant, Bristlebane<br><font color=0000AE><b>Malkar Zauviir</b></font> - 51st Elementalist, Bristlebane<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umanchyman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>manchyman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(6/28/01 9:49:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ooh, nice topic</span><hr size=1> After grouping up a few more times I did noticed the necro<br>
