<br>
Unless it's an arranged dual, your pet probably won't have a DS on it when the fighting breaks out.  Even if you're out looking for a fight, it's generally too much trouble to keep reapplying the damage shield while you look for people, and then when you come over a hill and they're looking at you, there's no time.<br>
<br>
Firepet is the ultimate pet killer, for that reason.  Pets are fast but low damage hitters, which is perfect for a big damage shield.  The necro could dispell the firepet's shield, but while he's doing that, you're busy doing something more directly damaging.<br>
<br>
Interesting that air pets do so well, though.  I favor air pets in PvP sometimes because their run speed is a little faster than the rest.  Nice to know they'll still do better than water or earth if it comes time to pick a fight with another pet.<br>
